<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>New World, the • new world</xh5><p> <i>New World, the—</i>North and South America: The bird which we call turkey was one of our best acclimatizations after the discovery of <u>the New World</u>.</p><p> <i>new world—</i>new setting of existence with its customs, traditions, etc.: She left her rich, safe, home and came to a <u>new world</u> in the city.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>brave new world, the</b>—a nightmarish utopian society, especially one in which technological progress has negative results: One only has to think of <u>the brave new world</u> as “prophetically” described by Aldous Huxley: societies made up of wilfully-created, genetically-determined master/slave creatures.</p> </entry>
